race.comment: Deep form race. Going with the promising TEQUISODA (8) who knuckled down strongly to get up for third when resuming over 1400m here last start. Improved second-up last prep to win his maiden at Hawkesbury. Will relish getting out to 1600m for the first time so more is to come. MIGNONETTE (9) has found the line well to finish just behind the placegetters in his two runs this time in work, both over much shorter journeys. Goes back from a wide draw but will be strong at the end of the mile. TOM CRUISING (3) has been unwanted in betting at his last two starts but won them both, the latest in a similar race to this 25 days ago. The handicapper may have caught up with him now but another big run will not surprise. OFF THE SCALE (7) had his chance but his condition gave out first-up over this trip at Newcastle. Drops 3kgs after the claim and with added fitness should give a good account. OTONO (5) was beaten less than a length in a BM68 here two back which is good form.
